reviews.headline: I love using this cleanser
reviews.comments: Easy, simple, effective cleanser! I used this every day for a week, and then every other day or so after to keep up on it. It's got a very pleasant texture and an easy squeeze tube, leaves my skin feeling soft and smelling clean!

reviews.headline: Acne-Treating Paste
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I like this acne paste. I haven't tried one before so this is my first time. It's such a cool thing to have a 3 in 1 as it's a cleanser, mask and spot treatment. The lather is nice and creamy when you use it. I like how it felt on my skin and how I was able to see some results after using it for awhile. It helped me clear up some blackheads

reviews.headline: Skin never felt so good
reviews.comments: I've been using this cleansing paste for a few weeks and really notice a difference in my skin. It feels gentle but still effective at reducing breakouts without leaving my face tight or dry. The texture is smooth and spreads easily, and a little goes a long way so the tube lasts. I also like that it has a light, fresh scent that isn't overwhelming. The packaging is simple and practical, easy to use without waste. Overall, a great balance between being effective and gentle, especially for sensitive acne-prone skin.

reviews.headline: Very nice product
reviews.comments: The Acne-Treating Cleansing Paste is gentle yet effective. It deeply cleanses without stripping, reduces breakouts, and leaves skin smoother and refreshed. With consistent use, it calms irritation and helps prevent new blemishes. A reliable daily skincare staple!

reviews.headline: I would recommend this product to friends!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] The wash is very gentle while effective on my skin and has helped with reduce any breakouts I had on my face. It's has a very soft texture and isn't too harsh on the skin. The scent wasn't strong either, and it's a good product for the price and worth getting. The packaging was also very simplistic and straightforward on how to use the wash.

reviews.headline: Combo of mask and cleanser
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This product is an interesting 2-in-1 concept, combining a cleanser and a mask. It does make my skin feel nice and clean and soft when I use it, without being over-stripped. Because of the clay content it is not the easiest to wash off andI also prefer salicylic acid in a leave-on product than something that washes off. If you're the kind of person who likes to spend time on your skincare, this could be really nice but I'll stick to my micellar water and toner.

reviews.headline: Works best as a cleanser
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] As someone who has struggled with acne for 10+ years, I'm always looking for something to help with my inevitable breakouts. I was excited to test this cleansing paste out, as it's marketed as a cleanser, mask, and treatment all in one. As a cleanser, it is smooth and slippery, but doesn't foam much and it leaves skin feeling a bit dry. As a mask, it goes on smoothly, but never fully dries - it stays as a paste. I was using it as a spot treatment for a while and it would end up on my pillowcase in the morning. As for effectiveness, it didn't dry up my active breakouts as much as I wanted it to. It maybe took the redness down slightly. If your skin reacts well to salicylic acid, this could be a great product for you.

reviews.headline: If you have stubborn acne, this is for you!
reviews.comments:
First of all a mask or a spot treatment? Kiehls has done it again. Lately, I've been experiencing some hormonal acne and this has been the only thing to clear it up! 

Don't walk, run and get this!

reviews.headline: Gentle cleanser
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This cleanser is very gentle on my sensitive skin and didn't cause any major reactions. I like how it's multi purpose however I didn't see too much of a change in my skin. It might take more time for me to see true results but it hasn't made my skin worse

reviews.headline: Overall great product
reviews.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] If you're looking for a single product that can cleanse, treat, and clarify without drying you out, this paste is a smart pick. It's especially great if dryness or irritation usually holds you back from using stronger acids. Plus, the option to use it as a mask or targeted spot treatment gives it real flexibility.As a cleanser, it's creamier than typical salicylic washes. It lathers gently and doesn't leave my skin feeling stripped or tight—a real plus for a BHA product.
As a mask, I applied a thicker layer for 10 minutes; my skin felt balanced afterward—less puffy and smoother without the usual tightness.
As a spot treatment, applying it overnight helped reduce the size and redness of breakouts noticeably by morning.

reviews.headline: Self Care Staple
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Yes! Yes! Yes! This is a great product to use weekly for your face routine. The perfect self care product. Very easy to use. Doesn't small bad and pulled all the yucky stuff out of my skin. I would get it again and again.

reviews.headline: Recommend
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I always get breakouts around the time of my period, and it seriously drives me crazy. Nothing ever seems to help, and most cleansers either don't work or leave my skin feeling super dry. But this one surprised me — it actually does the job! My skin feels clean but still soft, and the breakouts are way less noticeable. I'm really happy I gave it a try.

reviews.headline: Effective for troubled skin
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I had a mild break out about a week ago and used the Kiehl's Acne Treating Cleansing Paste a try. I double cleansed my face and used this paste as a mask, targeting areas prone to beak out. I incorporated this routine for a few days and the results were very noticeable. My blemishes looked less irritated and prevented new ones from forming. I wouldn't use this product every day for my sensitive skin, but I will keep using once a week as a cleanser for a deeper cleanse or as a wipe off mask when I have break outs.

reviews.headline: It's Good not Great
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] The best way to describe this product is that it is a GOOD product. It's not a life changingly amazing face wash, but it also gets the job done. I appreciate that as an acne product, it doesn't dry my face out or leave it feeling striped. It's very gentle, doesn't really have a scent, and didn't irritate my sensitive skin. I didn't really notice much difference with my breakouts or acne around my chin and I didn't feel like my skin changed for the better or worse. I don't have any complaints or true praises, like I said, it's just good.

reviews.headline: Somewhat effective
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I really like that is product is a 3 in 1 and think it would be really helpful for major breakouts. I tried it on a few breakouts and didn't notice much of a difference but I still think it could've been helping keep inflammation down.

reviews.headline: Great multi-use facial cleanser!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This stuff is so useful in a lot of ways! As you can see I have large pores so I was able to use it as a mask as well. It doesn't dry your face out which is nice and cleans really well. It doesn't have a scent to it. I really liked this product it and would use it again!

reviews.headline: I would definitely buy this again!!!
reviews.comments: This was an amazing product! It definitely cleared my skin within 2-3 weeks earlier than it claims. This product was overall a great face mask and if you want to try a face mask that clears your acne and also it smells good as well. If you have acne!

reviews.headline: Overall Good Gentle Cleanser
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I overall really liked this product! It's very gentle on your skin and isn't drying. There is minimal scent which is great. My face feels very soft after cleansing with it.

reviews.headline: Recommend
reviews.comments: I always get breakouts around the time of my period, and it seriously drives me crazy. Nothing ever seems to help, and most cleansers either don't work or leave my skin feeling super dry. But this one surprised me — it actually does the job! My skin feels clean but still soft, and the breakouts are way less noticeable. I'm really happy I gave it a try.

reviews.headline: Soft but effective
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This product is soft on your skin but tough on acne and blackheads. You can mix and match how you apply and use it from a scrub to a mask. It knocked the dirt right out of my pores and left my skin clean and smooth.

faceoff_positive.comments:
I was thrilled to have the opportunity to try the new cleansing paste from Kiehl's, a versatile 3-in-1 treatment that offers the benefits of a cleanser, mask, and spot treatment. This multifunctional product is particularly appealing for those who prefer simplicity in their skincare routine. Its ability to serve multiple purposes means that it can effectively address a range of skin concerns, making it a valuable addition to any beauty arsenal, especially for individuals looking to streamline their regimen.

As someone with sensitive skin, I approached the cleansing paste with caution, but I was pleasantly surprised by the results. The formula did not dry my skin out or cause any adverse reactions, which is often a concern for those with similar skin types. Instead, I experienced a mild and soothing effect during application. After just one use, I noticed a visible improvement in my skin's texture, which is a promising indication of this product's effectiveness.

The cleansing paste delivered noticeable results in clearing my skin and reducing the appearance of pores and blackheads. These common concerns can often be frustrating and challenging to manage, but this treatment made a significant difference. I appreciate that Kiehl's has created a product that is not only gentle but also powerful enough to tackle these issues effectively. Overall, I am grateful for the chance to try this remarkable product and look forward to incorporating it into my routine.
faceoff_positive.headline: Great new 3-in-1

faceoff_negative.comments: I received this product in exchange for my honest review. The left is the before and the right is the after. The face wash was nice and creamy. I did try it each way the influencer package said to. It made my skin feel great after because it didn't strip my skin of all my oils so I didn't feel the need to moisturize like some face washes do. It doesn't really lather like the advertisement showed but it's not a big deal because it is essentially a clay mask. It also doesn't completely dry like some masks where you can crack your face and it hurts a little. It does dry enough that I can put it on my acne spots and not worry that it's going to run away on my pillows. The scent was barely there if at all. I don't think I would buy this for a regular face wash because I do like my product to be sudsy but it's a nice face mask. My skin does look better, a little more glowy but I was also testing a face wash at the same time. I can't say that this was all due to kiehls.  I still got my hormonel acne which sucks but it is what it is.
faceoff_negative.headline: Not your regular face wash
